      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2019-09-20</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2020-02-14T15:10:42Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Protecting Critical Infrastructure Against Drones and Emerging Threats Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) to address issues related to terrorism threats of unmanned aircraft systems (drones) and other emerging terrorism threats.</p> <p>Specifically, DHS must</p> <ul> <li>request additional information from other federal, state, local, and private sector agencies&nbsp;relating to such threats associated with new technologies; </li> <li>develop and disseminate a terrorism threat assessment regarding drones and other emerging terrorism threats associated with such new technologies; and </li> <li>establish and utilize a secure communications and information technology infrastructure, including data-mining and other advanced analytical tools.</li></ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-09-20T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
        <item>
